Hi all, we have 3 models in this one for BFG Eldar factions

We have
1, Void Dragon Class Grand Cruiser (No icons so pick your eldar faction)
2,The Flame of Asuryan which is Prince Yriel Flag ship, belonging to craft world Iyanden, so this on has the Logo of the Iyanden craft world
3, Shadow Point which is part of the Ulthwe craft world, as this ship is more expensive then the Flame of Asuryan, Ive made it stand out with it having 5 Sails, (This model i would recommend printing in the 3 pieces and orientate almost vertical for the 2 side pods to reduce the number of supports on the sails, but if you think you can print it as 1 piece feel free to try using the complete version

Ive added a SMOOTH SAIL version of all 3 ships, just look at the name description for SMOOTH SAIL at the end for that version

Ive printed these in resin in a old resin printer (no 4k here and still they came out great)

The wings when printing in resin as it is thin will try warping slightly, once you have cured the wings in light, heat the wings with a hair dry to allow you to bend back into shape, I used my table as the flat surface and held the wing there until it had cooled to be back straight again

A pre-Fall Elfdar luxury cruiser. What I imagine the Elfdar would have used when they just wanted to enjoy the feeling of sailing - the Sunjammer. About as pretty and as detailed as I can manage.

So, why something off-the-wall like this? My mother has been fighting cancer for the past few years and it has now become inoperable. When she was younger she used to sail in little boats called Lasers, which were tiny, fragile, fast things. Her boat was called Tiny Dancer (like the Elton John song). Hence when I decided I'd do something to remember her by, I decided on a very fast Eldar ship.

Could I ask as many of you as possible to print one out, so that all over the world there would be some memory of her? Can I also ask that no-one sticks a gun on this, it would just feel wrong.

If you would like to donate, she's said she'd wants to support Macmillan, who have been really lovely helping her out:
https://www.justgiving.com/macmillan

The usual shtick, I am not affiliated with GW in any way! I know it's a bit cheeky to do this but it means a lot to me. Please don't reupload this on Shapeways and the like for commercial use (though you're welcome to upload them to get them printed that way for yourself).

This is a mix of Italianmoose's (https://www.thingiverse.com/Italianmoose/about) and Corvus Obscurus's (https://www.thingiverse.com/Corvus_Obscurus/about) eldar cruisers, to create a simple to assemble Void Stalker. The hull is a mishmash of Italianmoose's cruiser, while the wings are from Corvus's light cruiser.

This is modeled at about 80% of what *I* think the size should be. Although I can't tell how big the original was because I don't have one, this model gets close I'm guessing.

The upper and lower wings are halves, print two of each file. They are identical on each half as well as the left/right wing, so gluing them together for filament prints won't be hard. They fit on the model at a right-angel block, so again, easy assembly.
